\b\fs24 3. Installation\b0\fs20\par
\par
ignitionServer should have come with an installer. This installer runs on Windows 95, 98, Me, \par
2000, XP, and 2003. (NOTE: the ignitionServer Monitor runs on all platforms now!)\par
\par
This _might_ run under UNIX/Linux with Wine, but you will have to play with it yourself (i.e. do\par
not post to the support tracker; WE CAN NOT HELP YOU!)\par
\par
After installing ignitionServer, you will need to configure it. To do this, browse to where you\par
installed ignitionServer and open ircx.conf in Notepad. To change the Message of the Day, edit\par
ircx.motd in Notepad.\par
\par
Remember to disable X:DIE in your ircx.conf file. Failure to do so WILL result in messages like\par
"server misconfigured". This is a safety measure, so people don't just use default installs, which \par
usually have O: lines with passwords like "admin".\par
