\b\fs24 4. Frequently Asked Questions\b0\fs20\par
\par
Older versions of ignitionServer were a bit easier to use/modify than this current version. This\par
version is MUCH more powerful, has more than enough commands to be useful, and is quite a bit\par
less buggy. Please make sure you read this FAQ before you post to the support tracker.\par
\par
\b Q: When I start ignitionServer, nothing comes up!\b0\par
A: It's supposed to do this! ignitionServer now runs as a full-fledged daemon. You will not get\par
   any interface at all (unless you are on Windows NT and you installed the ignitionServer\par
   Monitor). If you are not sure you started it properly, start your IRC client and type:\par
     /server localhost\par
   If you connect to something, the server is running. A less time-intensive method would be to\par
   hit Ctrl-Alt-Del and see if the ignitionServer process is running.\par
\par
\b Q: Why doesn't ignitionServer start?\b0\par
A: First, make sure you read the above question. Then, check the following things:\par
   1) Is ircx.conf in the same folder as ignitionServer?\par
   2) Did I modify ircx.conf improperly?\par
   3) Is ircx.conf named properly (it must be ircx.conf -- do not capitalize the extension or any\par
      other part of the name!)?\par
   If you diagnosed those things and still have a problem, make sure ignitionServer isn't running\par
   as another process (Ctrl-Alt-Del). ignitionServer will only start one time. All other times it\par
   will not allow it.\par
\b\par
Q: Why does ignitionServer send out Closing Link: (AutoKilled: Server Misconfigured [see ircx.conf])\par
   and disconnect users on connection?\b0\par
A: A new feature was introduced to stop incorrectly configured servers to be used. (E.G. Using Default \par
   A Lines). To disable this feature simply find X:DIE in ircx.conf file and change the 1 to a 0\par
\par
\b Q: What operating system is reccommended to run ignitionServer?\b0\par
A: We reccommend you use Windows NT 4, Windows 2000, Windows XP, or Windows Server 2003. Windows\par
   95/98/ME is not reccommended at all.\par
\par
